  "text": "Applications attempting to use raw receptor data directly will have great difficulty functioning correctly without significant preprocessing of the data to account for its unreliability. As this data cleaning will be common across most applications, one possible solution would be to use standard data warehouse-style cleaning. Data cleaning in warehouses is usually an offline, centralized, iterative, and sometimes interactive process that focuses on tasks such as transformations, matching, and duplicate elimination [CITATION_1] . Such an approach, however, is ill-suited for receptor data.",
